To compile my code, load a terminal, cd into the right directory, place jflex-1.6.1.jar in the same directory and enter the following commands into the terminal:

java -jar jflex-1.6.1.jar Lex.flex
javac *.java

The first command creates a file called Lex.java. The second compiles all of the .java files. To run my syntax checker, use the following command:

java SyntaxChecker [filename]

Replace [filename] with the name of a .foo file containing foo language code.

If the file contains code written with valid foo syntax, the program's output will be:

hardy:~/Desktop/470/proj2> java SyntaxChecker test01_main_1.foo
Success

If the file contains at least 1 syntax error, the program's output will be:

hardy:~/Desktop/470/proj2> java SyntaxChecker test01_main_err1.foo
Error: Syntax error

